<!DOCTYPE assessment PUBLIC "-//Carnegie Mellon University//DTD Assessment MathML 2.4//EN" "http://oli.web.cmu.edu/dtd/oli_assessment_mathml_2_4.dtd"><assessment xmlns:cmd="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/content/metadata/2.1/" id="_u10_intro_quiz" recommended_attempts="1" max_attempts="6"><title>Endocrine Structures and Functions</title><page id="f1dccbdf1ce1410893271e1f27704380"><multiple_choice id="q1" grading="automatic" select="single"><body><p id="afbda110ce088442587407e9ed8f8802c">Which of the following are functions of the endocrine system?</p></body><input shuffle="false" id="def784ca7ad8474ba49e24f8f0c171e3" labels="false"><choice value="A">Growth</choice><choice value="B">Development</choice><choice value="C">Adaptation</choice><choice value="D">All of the above</choice></input><part id="q1_p1"><skillref idref="endo_functions_LO_SKILL" /><response match="A" score="0"><feedback><p id="acbcacbec557c49bcb1480145f260a1d5">Partially correct. Growth is just one of several functions of the endocrine system.</p></feedback></response><response match="B" score="0"><feedback><p id="aabfe6d60516d4977b4651f7e5349314e">Partially correct. Development is just one of several functions of the endocrine system.</p></feedback></response><response match="C" score="0"><feedback><p id="ad745d7d877ef4aeea1c935881f55a21e">Partially correct. Adaptation is just one of several functions of the endocrine system.</p></feedback></response><response match="D" score="10"><feedback><p id="aa5290468775f49e7a29b3fd7d8139492">Correct. Growth, development, and adaptation are all functions of the endocrine system.</p></feedback></response></part></multiple_choice><multiple_choice id="q2" grading="automatic" select="single"><body><p id="aada3a9749d1b4b81a92319845e3a38c9">Which of the following is a condition representing underactive thyroid?</p></body><input shuffle="true" id="f999fae0efac475aa92f23366d21368d" labels="false"><choice value="A">Diabetes</choice><choice value="B">Osteoporosis</choice><choice value="C">Hyperthyroidism</choice><choice value="D">Hypothyroidism</choice></input><part id="q2_p1"><skillref idref="endo_functions_LO_SKILL" /><response match="A" score="0"><feedback><p id="ad8a2a2a59a824d7985bd402d435f2b5c">Incorrect. Diabetes is a result of not being able to control glucose levels.</p></feedback></response><response match="B" score="0"><feedback><p id="ab54dff2826c442718fc244b891369bf9">Incorrect. Osteoporosis is a result of too little calcium in the bones.</p></feedback></response><response match="C" score="0"><feedback><p id="ae52977a2bf0f4ba0bea084df83e0bce9">Incorrect. Hyperthyroidism is a disorder caused by the excess activity of the thyroid gland.</p></feedback></response><response match="D" score="10"><feedback><p id="acf6054c810864ea683e272eb9c0d7928">Correct. Hypothyroidism is a disorder caused by the decreased activity of the thyroid gland.</p></feedback></response></part></multiple_choice></page></assessment>
